cs.CL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on generating natural language sequences from source code snippets using sequence-to-sequence models.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses applications such as code summarization and documentation, which are relevant to software engineering.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new approach for encoding source code using the syntactic structure of programming languages and uses attention mechanisms.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks for generating natural language sequences from source code.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a possible category as the paper leverages the syntactic structure of programming languages to better encode source code.
